## ✅ Data Quality Team — Complete!

All 5 YAML files pass `yaml.safe_load` validation. Here's what was created:

### 📁 Directory Structure
```
/workspace/team2/
├── recipe/
│   ├── data-quality-team.yaml          ← Team orchestrator recipe (104 lines)
│   ├── sub/
│   │   ├── sub_data-profiler.yaml      ← 📊 Sub-agent: dataset analyzer (24 lines)
│   │   ├── sub_anomaly-detector.yaml   ← 🔍 Sub-agent: outlier/dup finder (24 lines)
│   │   └── sub_quality-reporter.yaml   ← 📋 Sub-agent: quality scorer (24 lines)
│   └── instructions/
│       ├── sub_data-profiler.md        ← Detailed profiling workflow (107 lines)
│       ├── sub_anomaly-detector.md     ← Detailed anomaly detection (102 lines)
│       └── sub_quality-reporter.md     ← Detailed score computation (140 lines)
├── .state/
│   └── workflows.yaml                  ← Task workflows & agent registry (243 lines)
└── tools/
```

### 🧠 3 Sub-Agents

| Sub-Agent | Role | Scores |
|---|---|---|
| **📊 data-profiler** | Analyzes CSV/JSON — rows, columns, data types, missing values per column | PROFILE |
| **🔍 anomaly-detector** | Finds outliers (IQR/Z-score), exact/partial duplicates, integrity issues | DETECT |
| **📋 quality-reporter** | Synthesizes findings → quality score 0-100 + rating + recommendations | REPORT |

### 📊 Quality Score Formula
| Component | Weight | Based on |
|---|---|---|
| Completeness | 30% | Missing value analysis |
| Consistency | 25% | Integrity issues |
| Uniqueness | 20% | Duplicate rate |
| Accuracy | 15% | Outlier rate |
| Structural | 10% | Schema quality |

Rating: 🟢 Excellent (90+) → 🟡 Good (70-89) → 🟠 Fair (50-69) → 🔴 Poor (25-49) → ⚫ Critical (0-24)

### 🔧 How to Use
The team orchestrator (`data-quality-team.yaml`) accepts modes: `FULL` (all 3 agents), `QUICK` (skip anomaly detection), `PROFILE_ONLY`, or `ANOMALY_ONLY`. Delegate to it with a `file_path` and it runs the pipeline, returning a complete quality report.
